IL took care of payments to the government. And for their contribution, ONGC/OIL got a share in the exploration blocks, as in Cairn. You could argue that the royalty payments by ONGC wouldnt be much higher than the amounts it will earn as a 30% partner in Cairn. That may be true, but this was a risk both ONGC and the private firms took. And, as the note prepared by ONGC for the Kirit Parikh expert group makes clear, it was always understood the government would make good this lossindeed, a Committee of Secretaries and a Group of Ministers even made this recommendation in 1997-98. So the government is actually trying to get the foreign oil companies to honour its commitment. Thats both bad news and bad in law.
