vides the opportunity to be involved in multi-disciplinary, translational research and training activities with new collaborators from academic, policy and commercial organisations, which will shape the development of a low carbon future within the region and beyond.Also, it will offer scholars and academicians a chance to make an impact with low carbon solutions in society. Meanwhile, the centre can leverage funds from regional, national, European government and research councils. The centre is creating teams of natural scientists, engineers and social scientists, working across traditional boundaries, in a research centre developed in close liaison with private and public sector stakeholders.It will draw on the expertise of world-class researchers in the region as a focal point for understanding and demonstrating how business can evolve and adapt in a low-carbon world. In fact, by conducting \u2018translational\u2019 research into clean technologies, the centre will be a conduit for the practical application of low carbon technologies, helping both to attract inward investment and enhance business growth and economic output.
