d and liquor. Some revellers, braving the cold and chill even spent their night partying on the river bank to see the first sun rise of the New Year.In fact, celebrations had started well in advance on December 31 night with people hurrying home and then proceeding to parties, gathering and outing beating away both the weather and recession blues.Special arrangements were made by the district administarion and police to thwart any untoward incident.
