untries could take over the mandate at the cost of the UN Framework Convention on Climate Change which hosts the Kyoto Protocol too.The BASIC countries had already gone back on their earlier red lines at Copenhagen not insisting that all funds for climate change adaptation and mitigation to poor countries come from public finance and routed through the UN. But Pershing's statements in the US further strengthened the suspicion that the give aways had only begun and not ended at Copenhagen and that India could expect to give in more in the hectic negotiations slated for 2010.
