tural gas but also moving towards a more efficient coal regime. The FMs commitment to secure legislative approval for auctioning captive coal blocks would gradually align domestic coal prices with international ones, as well as make cleaner energy sources more competitive. China has simultaneously announced that its working on a programme to ensure that 15% of its total consumption mix will come from clean energy by 2020. IPCC must be given some credit for why Chindia have become more proactive on climate change, turning around from their the developed countries must fix what they broke focus to become constructively occupied with breeding domestic low-carbon policies. In continuing to advance in this direction, they could do with a stronger, more rigorous and credible IPCC.
