ne sectoral committees that would work on nine different impact areas of climate change.\u000a\u000aThese areas include health and social vulnerability, energy, transport, agriculture, urban development, water resources, coastal and disaster, mining and forest among others. Meanwhile, eleven working groups headed by the secretaries have held one round of discussion with the experts from March 1-6.
