y chairman Montek Singh Ahluwalia on Sunday said that although growth in Indias industrial production has been lower than expected we should not become judgmental based on monthly numbers. The latest data shows that Index of Industrial Production (IIP), which stands as a measure of factory output, grew 4.4% in September this year against the same month last year. The growth in IIP has been lower than expected. But lets see how it goes for the rest of the year, Ahluwalia told reporters on the sidelines of India Economic Summit.\u000a\u000aHowever, he said the slowing growth in IIP is unlikely to hinder the economic growth. We should not become judgmental based on monthly numbers. I still believe that our earlier projection of 8.5% economic growth will hold for the entire year, he said.
