g climate change will be rejected and such attempts would seriously jeopardise collaboration on both climate negotiations as well as international trade.\u000a\u000aIn a bid to unite all the developing countries,which have at present grouped themselves in different blocs,the ministers of BASIC nations had invited representatives from a large number of other countries for the meeting. The joint statement therefore incorporated the concerns of these countries as well.\u000a\u000aFor all the latest News Archive News, download Indian Express App
