te Change.\u000a\u000aThe state government has already identified nodal departments and formed core groups for each mission. Each core group comprises members from various government departments,experts of GSI/remote sensing,engineering institutions,IITs and research institutions.\u000a\u000a“So far,we have only prepared the draft action plan for National Mission on Strategic Knowledge for Climate Change. For the others,only action points has been finalised. The GTZ will prepare a comprehensive state action plan covering all these missions,” said Singh.\u000a\u000aIn the draft action plan for National Mission on Strategic Knowledge,the core group,among others,has proposed publication of journals on climate change,integration of climate change agenda with national green corps activities and district plan activities,creation of awareness centre at national parks,sanctuaries,zoo and other public places,promotion of centre for excellence in universities and institutions and funding climate change research.\u000a\u000aFor all the latest Lucknow News, download Indian Express App
